==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Deism
<hw>De"ism</hw> <pr>(d⟦emac⟧"⟦icr⟧z'm)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>deus</ets> god: cf. F. <ets>d⟦eacute⟧isme</ets>. See
<er>Deity</er>.]</ety> <def>The doctrine or creed of a deist; the belief
or system of those who acknowledge the existence of one God, but deny
revelation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ <ex>Deism</ex> is the belief in natural religion only,
or those truths, in doctrine and practice, which man is to discover by
the light of reason, independent of any revelation from God. Hence,
<ex>deism</ex> implies <consof>infidelity</consof>, or a disbelief in
the divine origin of the Scriptures.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Deist</ent>⟦br⟧
